# Cloudflare Pages SPA-style rewrite for the recipient walkthrough.
#
# Real files (anything Next.js exports under out/, including /about/,
# /terms/, /privacy/, /walkthrough/, /_next/*, /favicon.ico, etc.) are
# served first. Only requests that don't match a real file fall through
# to these rules, so this is safe.
#
# Recipient URLs look like /:src/:tgt/:encodedText[?theme=:theme] — any
# path with at least three segments. We rewrite them (status 200, URL
# preserved in the address bar) to the walkthrough shell, which parses
# window.location.pathname client-side.

/:src/:tgt/* /walkthrough/ 200
